title: For Sale:  1967 Savage  Anchutz Mark 10 22
location: Rocky Mount, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: This is a very beautiful 1967 Savage Anschutz 22LR.  When I got it, it was like new with no indications it had ever been fired.  I set it up for 50 to 300 yard shooting to teach one class in basic ballistics....made 4 trips to the range to set it up and test it for about 200 rounds....then about about 300 rounds were fired the class.....then it just sat on top of my case.  I need to make some space so I have a couple of 22 rifles up for sale.   Perfect crown, like new metal, few marks on the bolt, very light signs of use on the stock.    The scope has 6 bolt quick detachable rings mounted on a EGW 20 MOA rail.   This returns the scope to less than 1 MOA if you follow consistent procedures.....often returns to exactly the same zero....I remember remounting the scope and being about an inch off then remounting again more carefully and it being dead on.  I am surprised at how consistently this set up returns to zero when you switch from irons to scope. The 20 moa rail is removable as it mounts with 6 set screws.  The receiver is NOT drilled and tapped for scope, it has a dovetail rail.  The original Savage Anschutz peep / aperture sight and also a Williams FP target low sight are included and can both be mounted as the mounting bolts for the Savage / Anschutz sight and the base for the Williams sight are the same size.   The Willimas sight uses the base.  Remove the base and the original sight mounts directly to the receiver with out the base.  The scope is a Bushnell 6-24 Mill dot and is surprisingly good...no it is not a Nightforce....but really good for the money....you will have no problem making squirrel headshots at 100.   Scope is like new with the box and papers.  Original swivel slings with one additional standard swivel stud mounted through the bottom rail.....this is so a bipod can be mounted.   A blackhawk cheek pad was resewn to fit this rifle.  The riser is removable so you have good cheek weld and eye position with either iron sights or scope.   The peeps are std .050 target apertures and the hooded front sight has a aperture  insert suitable for hunting or std targets at 50 or 100.   The rifle (metal) was manufactured in Germany by Anschutz with the Anschutz model 64 receiver.   Only the stock was made by Savage.   Theses were sold for a few years in the USA as Savage/Anschutz, and in Europe a Anschutz/Savage.  The beautiful stock always got gawkers.  More photos here: https://1drv.ms/f/s!Au11snxSmYXRhjj1HZF9tcBxA_Yo
